                        Stuart
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d476</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">476</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-11-17T04:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-11-17T04:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-17T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-17T04:00:00-05:00" n="476" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.002/11–1748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-17T17:00:00+08:00">November 17, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:52 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2242. Hu Shih<note n="21" xml:id="d476fn21">Chancellor of the National Peking
                        University.</note> told me yesterday that he is prepared to accept
                    premiership of National Government if three conditions are fulfilled: (1) that
                    US President or Secretary State make public statement of moral support of
                    National Government; (2) that American economic <pb facs="0594" n="584" xml:id="pg_584"/> and military assistance be stepped up; (3) that he be
                    given free hand to pick his own Cabinet.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, pouched Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
